  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
        <div rend="parallel">
            <lg xml:id="TK19">
<l>tāṉan tavamiraṇṭun taṅkā viyaṉulakam</l>
<l>vāṉam vaḻaṅkā teṉiṉ</l>            
            </lg>
            <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>The two, giving and austerity, would disappear in the wide world</l>
<l>if heaven stopped doing what it does.</l>
            </lg>
        </div>
    </body>
  </text>
  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
      <head>Parimēlaḻakar</head>
      <div rend="parallel">
        <p xml:id="TK19_P1">
          (i-ḷ). akaṉṟa vulakiṉkaṇ tāṉamun tavamumākiya viraṇṭaṟamum uḷavākā, maḻai peyyātāyiṉ, (e - ṟu).
        </p>
        <p xml:lang="en">
          The meaning ... : The two dharmas, namely donation and austerity, would not exist on the extensive Earth if rain did not pour.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div rend="parallel">
        <p xml:id="TK19_P2">
          tāṉamāva taṟaneṟiyāṉ vanta poruḷkaḷait takkārkkuvakaiyōṭuṅkoṭuttal. tavamāvatu maṉam poṟivaḻi pōkātu niṟṟaṟporuṭṭu virataṅkaḷā ṉuṇṭicurukkal mutalāyiṉa. perumpāṉmaipaṟṟittāṉam illaṟattiṉmēlum tavam tuṟavaṟattiṉ mēlum niṉṟaṉa.
        </p>
        <p xml:lang="en">
          Donation means giving articles of wealth that have come [to one] through moral means to worthy [recipients] in every way(?). Austerity means the halting of the mind without its going [out] through [the portals of] the senses, vows concerning(?) possessions, the curtailment of food, etc. For (more lit. "concerning") the majority, donation has been established within [the realm of] the dharma of the house[holder], while austerity [has been established] within [the realm of] renunciation.
        </p>
      </div>
    </body>
  </text>
  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
      <head>Maṇakkuṭavar (12)</head>
      <div rend="parallel">
        <p xml:id="TK19-M1">
          (i - ḷ.) tāṉamun tavamumākiya viraṇṭaṟamu muḷavākā; akaṉṟa vulakattukkaṇ maḻai peyyātāyiṉ, (e - ṟu).
        </p>
        <p xml:lang="en">
          The meaning ... : The two dharmas, namely donation and austerity, would not exist if rain did not pour upon the extensive Earth.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div rend="parallel">
        <p xml:id="TK19-M2">
          itu tāṉamun tavamuṅ keṭumeṉṟatu.
        </p>
        <p xml:lang="en">
          This means that donation and austerity would perish.
        </p>
      </div>
    </body>
  </text>
